-- Bulgaria c.bank asks for Corpbank rescue plans by end-August
-- By Angel Krasimirov
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 08:29AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 22 (Reuters) - Bulgaria's central bank has asked the two biggest shareholders of troubled Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) <6C9.BB> to present plans for the bank's rescue by the end of this month.

The central bank said it had sent letters to the two shareholders on Friday, adding their proposals should be in line with national and EU legislation.